              "type": "ref",
              "ref": "69r4N",
              "name": "Skill 2 - Sales Team",
              "width": 853,
              "descendants": {
                "EaVOv": {
                  "height": 44
                },
                "V2U5E": {
                  "content": "about-sales-team/SKILL.md",
                  "fill": "#847b73"
                },
                "FBW20": {
                  "content": "---\nname: about-sales-team\ndescription: How to perform analytics for sales and GTM-related areas\n---\n\n# Sales\n\n## Overview\n\nThe sales team is broken down into sub-teams for inbound sales, outbound sales, and enterprise sales. The Enterprise Sales owns all accounts at the enterprise level (>1,000 employees) and includes both the inbound and outbound directions for this level.\n\nWe use Salesforce to manage our sales operations. The most important tables are `dim_salesforce_opportunities` and `dim_salesforce_accounts`. \n\n## Key Concepts\n\n### Opportunity Types\n* **New Business:** First-time purchase by a new account.\n* **Expansion:** Upsell or cross-sell to an existing account.\n* **Renewal:** Continuation of an existing contract.\n...",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "fontSize": "$code_font_size"
                }
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
